<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="266" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="17.[794,1393,1895,2318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[799,954,1895,1924]" pageId="17" pageNumber="266">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas, 1892" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bulleri">Geomys bulleri Thomas, 1892</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="17" pageNumber="266">“Talpa, Mascota, Jalisco [Mexico], 8500 feet.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[794,1393,1895,2318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="266">
Molecular studies suggest that the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[800,965,2053,2082]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Pappogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pappogeomys</taxonomicName>
1s sister to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Cratogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cratogeomys</taxonomicName>
. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Russell" authorityYear="1957" box="[1157,1244,2092,2121]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Pappogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alcorni">alcorni</taxonomicName>
was previously recognized at the species level but was regarded as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" box="[1270,1348,2167,2200]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bulleri">bulleri</taxonomicName>
by J. W. Demastes and colleagues in 2003. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
